Kia Ora, Grant,
On 1 July 2025 I requested a copy of my full claim file under the =
Privacy Act 2020 (including assessments, communications, and =
inventories). I understand Tower is required to provide this within 20 =
working days, which has now passed. Could you please update me on the =
progress of my request, or confirm if I should direct this to Tower=E2=80=99=
s Privacy Officer?

In addition, given that the claim is still progressing, I would =
appreciate it if Tower could provide me with updated copies of my full =
claim file on at least a monthly basis. This will help ensure accuracy =
and transparency as new assessments and documents are generated.

I value your assistance on this matter and would prefer to resolve it =
directly with your help. Please let me know the next steps.

Ng=C4=81 mihi,

Raffaella


> On 1 Jul 2025, at 11:31=E2=80=AFPM, Raffaella del Prete =
<raffaellanz@icloud.com> wrote:
>=20
> Hi Sasha  and Chris,
>=20
> I saw that you've recently tried to get in touch earlier today, =
unfortunately I was unable to attend your calls.. For clarity and =
consistency, can we please have  all communication from this point =
forward be conducted by email only?=20
>=20
> I would appreciate your attention to the following:
>=20
> Claim Updates and Forward Plan:
> Could you elease provide a current update and clear next steps for =
both of my claims: House (C90306048) and Contents (C90306256.This should =
include any scopes of work, contractor involvement, decisions pending, =
and expected timeframes.=20
>=20
> Also can we agree that you will send updates on both every week so =
that we can ensure alignment and progress?
>=20
> Privacy Act Request =E2=80=93 Full Claim Files:
> Under the Privacy Act 2020, I formally request a full copy of my file =
for both claims (C90306048 and C90306256). This includes all internal =
notes, reports, third-party correspondence, scopes, assessments, emails, =
and any other material Tower holds in relation to these claims.
>=20
> Claims Preparation Costs & Structural Engineer:
> I would like to engage a structural engineer to assist with damage =
assessment. Please confirm whether Tower requires prior approval of this =
engagement, and provide the policy guidelines or procedures for =
reimbursement of claims preparation work.
>=20
> Outstanding Expense Claim:
> I submitted an expense claim on 26 June, and I=E2=80=99ve not yet =
received any update or confirmation. Please advise on the status of this =
claim and when I can expect a response or reimbursement.
>=20
> Kind regards,
>=20
> Raffaella Del Prete
>=20


